text: As a college student, I was fortunate to hear Rev. Billy Graham speak. We mourn his passing but celebrate the lives he touched with the Gospel message. His teaching and ministry will continue to impact generations to come.

Testimony by top intelligence officials that Russia is targeting 2018 election and Robert Mueller's recent indictments are more evidence that we must take Russia threat seriously. I continue to support full implementation of the bipartisan sanctions bill Congress passed in 2017.

Our hearts are broken on this Valentine’s Day for the Stoneman Douglas High School community in Parkland, Florida. Words are inadequate to properly convey our condolences to those who lost a loved one today.
Great to join with leaders from around the world at the National Prayer Breakfast this morning. The life-changing power of prayer transcends geography, politics, and political issues.

I just read the memo written by Democrats on the House Intelligence Committee, and I hope that this minority report will be made public this week. With so much at stake, both the Nunes and Schiff memos should be available to all Americans. (1/3)

Ultimately, we must follow the truth, which is why it remains important for the Mueller investigation to continue without interruption. I also hope that the committee’s minority report will be released soon so that it too will be available to all Americans. #MemoDay
Amanda and I are on the train carrying GOP members to our annual retreat that just had an accident. We are okay, but please join us in praying for those injured and their families.

Tonight Congress passed legislation to fund the government until February 8 and end the current shutdown. This legislation is important for northeast Indiana. It stops the job-killing medical device tax for two years and extends CHIP funding for six years.
Senate Democrats are holding health coverage for 13,155 children in #IN03 who rely on CHIP hostage by not passing the CR that includes a 6 year reauthorization and funding. #Schumershutdown

Senate Democrats chose to shut down the government over DACA, which doesn’t expire until March. This reckless decision will hurt our men and women in uniform and create unnecessary chaos. Let’s prioritize those who serve our country over those who entered our country illegally.

Yesterday I spent time reviewing a classified report about the FBI/DOJ and the Trump campaign. The American people deserve to see the contents of this report, and I fully support its public disclosure. #ReleaseTheMemo

When some pushed for the return of earmarks last year, Speaker Ryan pledged to revisit the issue later through a transparent debate. To his credit, the Speaker's leadership at that time helped the Republican Conference avert a bad decision. (1/2)
Looking forward to watching @GovHolcomb give the #INSOTS tonight. A lot of momentum going into 2018 – it’s going to be a great year for Hoosiers.
Will be live with @tonykatz on @93WIBC around 7:40am to discuss the Iran protests and my resolution that condemns Iran’s government for violence against its citizens. Be sure to tune in!
Congrats on making it to the #VoiceFinale tonight @AddisonAgen. Wishing you the best of luck.
President Trump’s National Security Strategy is a welcome and forward-looking change away from the Obama administration’s ‘lead from behind’ approach. (1/3)
I’ll be cheering on @USF_Football as they defend their NAIA Football National Championship title tonight. Go Cougars!

The FY18 NDAA @POTUS signed today gives our troops their largest wage increase in nearly eight years, significantly boosts active duty end strength for each branch of service and increases funding for military facilities and new oversight tools.
The 127th #ArmyNavy game is this afternoon. As a Congressman, I am officially neutral, but I felt like wearing blue and gold today for some reason. #GoNavy #BeatArmy

It’s great to have a president who is finally enforcing the law passed by Congress in 1995 recognizing Jerusalem as the capital of #Israel. Today’s news re-affirms the special relationship between the United States and our cherished ally.

As we learn more about the poor behavior of many of our leaders in politics, media and entertainment, I am grateful to have @SusanWBrooks serving as Chairwoman of the House Ethics Committee. Her integrity and leadership are a bright light during a dark time.
Cheering on Fort Wayne native and top 11 finalist @AddisonAgen on @NBCTheVoice tonight. #IN03 is rooting for you!
The news this morning of a Navy plane crash in the Pacific is devastating. Relieved that eight sailors are in good condition and praying for the search of the missing three.

Glad to see Robert Mugabe resign as President of Zimbabwe. His rule was marked by human rights violations and economic repression. Hopefully the people of Zimbabwe can look toward a democratic and prosperous future.
Today on #NationalEntrepreneursDay, I applaud the innovation of #IN03 entrepreneurs like Chuck Surack of @SweetwaterSound who created his successful music business from scratch.
Live now with @WOWOFORTWAYNE. Tune in!
“Kindness is a language which the deaf can hear and the blind can see” – Mark Twain. Happy #WKD
Careers in science, technology, engineering, and medicine are among the fastest growing occupations in our country. Happy #StemDay.
#TaxReform will eliminate the death tax after 6 years → a huge win for family businesses and farms in #IN03.
Voted today to preserve the @indianadunes and officially rename it the “Indiana Dunes National Park.” A true Hoosier gem.
Praying for NYC after today's act of terror. We must stand united against terrorism.
On Reformation's 500th anniversary, I am thankful for life-changing power of Gospel & religious freedom we have as Americans #reformation500
1/ Months ago I & many other Republicans vowed to support Mueller investigation & allow it to work its way through process to get the facts
Congratulations to @CanterburyFW's boys soccer team on earning their 6th @ihsaa1 state championship last night!
1/ Yesterday I attended classified briefing from DoD officials re: Niger & agree too many questions remain unanswered about ambush on Oct. 4
Best wishes to @AddisonAgen on her @NBCTheVoice performance this evening. You make #IN03 proud.
(1/2) “Logic will get you from A to Z; imagination will get you everywhere.” – Albert Einstein #TuesdayThoughts
President Trump is right to call for a new policy on Iran and demand a change in the Iranian regime's behavior (1/4)
Wishing a very happy birthday to my friend @SteveScalise. Glad to have you back!
Congrats to Hoosier Ted McKinney on confirmation as @USDA Under Secretary of Agriculture for Trade and Foreign Agricultural Affairs.
Amanda and I are praying for a quick recovery for the injured and peace for the families of the victims in Las Vegas.
What a great & emotional moment to welcome our friend & colleague @SteveScalise back to the floor. May God continue to bless his recovery.
Looking forward to hearing @DonaldTrump speak on #taxreform that will level the playing field for Hoosier families & businesses.
Praying for those affected by devastation in Puerto Rico and thinking about our friends @RepJenniffer, @AngelMRivera and their families.
Happy new year to all those celebrating #RoshHashanah
Agree with @POTUS message at #UNGA calling out unacceptable behavior of Iran + North Korea, challenge to UN members to fulfill commitments
Today I voted for 2018 funding bill that would defund @PlannedParenthood, saving taxpayers $330M. Senate should prioritize #DefundPP effort.
Wishing a very happy Independence Day weekend to our Macedonian friends! #26YearsMacedonia
Raising the debt ceiling without significant spending reforms is not “draining the swamp."
Looking forward to tomorrow's @HarrisCorp visit w/ @NOAA’s Dr. Stephen Volz to discuss saving lives w/ next-gen weather forecasting tools.
My thoughts and prayers are with the victims of the #Barcelona attack. We must do all we can to eradicate terrorism around the globe.
All are created equal and endowed by their Creator with certain unalienable rights. We must reject white supremacy.
Whatever our political differences, we all must reject the hatred, bigotry, and racism on display in Charlottesville.
Wishing @CMStutzman a very happy birthday today. Thank you for your work to promote the sanctity of life in Indiana and across country.
I want to congratulate @RepTrey and his wife, Kelly, on the recent birth of their son. I hope you enjoy this special time as a family.
Given the readiness crisis our military faces, I agree with @POTUS that every resource provided to DoD should go to national security needs.
Today marks the 48th anniversary of @NASA’s #Apollo11 first manned moon landing #OTD #smallstep #giantleap
(1/4) One of the ongoing issues few are talking about is how Senate Democrats are obstructing important @POTUS nominees.
(1/3) While engaging Putin is necessary, partnering with Russia at the expense of our allies and national security is a mistake.
(1/7) A few thoughts on health care reform and its potential impact on #Hoosiers…
Happy birthday to @POTUS @realDonaldTrump. Grateful for his leadership on this difficult day.
Christopher Goff is staunch protector of the unborn and has utmost respect for rule of law-- pleased he has been named to IN Supreme Court.
The Dodd-Frank law has hurt Hoosier consumers, small businesses and families. Today I will vote for the #ChoiceAct to reverse this damage.
(1/3) In coming weeks, Congress will vote on whether to raise debt ceiling.
Ronald Reagan passed away 13 years ago today. His remarkable life and legacy continue to inspire us today.
A heartbreaking night in London. America stands united with our friends in Great Britain against terrorism and violence.
From the start, this agreement bypassed Congress and was more about President Obama's political climate agenda than sound science.
I am glad @POTUS is following through on his campaign promise and pulling the United States out of the flawed Paris agreement.
The US should recognize Jerusalem as rightful capital of Israel. This holy city is the most logical + efficient place to locate our embassy.
Happy race day to all Hoosiers. It's time for the 101st running of the Greatest Spectacle in Racing. #Indy500
To those celebrating this month in northeast Indiana and across our state, I wish you a Happy Ramadan filled with peace and joy.
Our thoughts and prayers are with those in Manchester and the U.K.
We've invested too much blood & treasure in Afghanistan to tolerate stalemate→ looking fwd to learning more abt President's troop plans.
1/3 Leader of our top law-enforcement agency must have American people's trust. Through questionable decisions, Director Comey lost it.
Director Comey lost the trust of both Rs and Ds. Our next FBI Director must be non-partisan and widely respected.
Yesterday I voted for the Korea Interdiction and Modernization of Sanctions Act → N Korea’s disastrous ambitions must be stopped, period.
Passage of AHCA important step in process of rolling back Obamacare, enacting free mkt reforms and improving country’s health care system.
I'm proud to cosponsor & vote for @RepMcSally's bill to bring Congress under #AHCA because Members should abide by the laws they pass.
Privileged to join my friend @SenToddYoung on the Senate floor as he delivered his maiden speech today.
2/2 As work begins on FY18 spending bills, I’m hopeful Congress will follow reg. budget order and work with Administration to cut spending.
1/2 Today I voted against a $1.1 trillion omnibus that fails to properly address $20 trillion national debt and reduce the size of fed govt.
More than 100 Hoosier businesses contributed to the USS Indiana submarine - the most advanced to have ever sailed. #SSN789
Pleased that my bill, HR 1390, to allow veterans to be buried closer to home passed subcommittee + will be considered by @HouseVetAffairs
I commend @POTUS for signing bill to extend Vets Choice program → sudden end could have left gap in vet health care. #ThursdayThoughts
Wishing all my fellow Indiana grads a Happy #IUDay today. Go Hoosiers!
The U.S. Navy has 270 ships; under Reagan we had abt 600. Today, our Navy can only meet 40% of Combatant Cdr requests. #WednesdayWisdom
Judge Gorsuch will be an outstanding addition to the Supreme Court and a steadfast defender of the Constitution.
Judge Neil Gorsuch is a strict constructionist who is well-qualified and will defend the rights of the unborn.
It is clear that majority of Dem opposition to Judge Gorsuch is unrelated to Judge Gorsuch. He will uphold Constitution and is best choice.
On this #VietnamVeteransDay 2017, thank you to all who faithfully served.
We should not turn a blind eye to Putin’s thuggish behavior in order to pursue cooperation with Russia.
Our government must affirm basic American values like free speech and the right to peaceful protest by voicing support for Russian people.
Russia’s crackdown on peaceful protests is shameful.
As a new member I spend more time than ever at airports and around @TSA ... tonight I helped pass 6 bills to strengthen TSA & @DHSgov.
Congrats to my friend + fellow Hoosier Dan Coats on being confirmed as Director of National Intelligence. We are grateful for his service.
Pleased to see the Senate vote today to confirm fellow #Hoosier Seema Verma to lead Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services. @CMSGov
I applaud @POTUS for initiating the process of streamlining govt agencies that arbitrarily regulate our businesses out of business.
I support @POTUS nomination of Alex Acosta for Labor Secretary. He will bring valuable experience to this important role.
These are common-sense proposals that would significantly improve the American Health Care Act.
.@RepMGriffith amendment would institute work requirements for able-bodied, childless adults on Medicaid.
.@MarshaBlackburn @RepJoeBarton amendment would freeze new enrollment in Obamacare’s Medicaid expansion at the end of 2017.
I strongly support positions taken today by @RepublicanStudy to support two amendments to GOP Obamacare replacement bill.
Happy 102nd birthday to my fellow Sailors in the U.S. @navy_reserve. Wishing you fair winds and following seas for 102 more!
The WOTUS rule is an example of Washington overreach that is affecting businesses, utilities, manufacturers + farmers across northeast IN.
I’m pleased to see @POTUS make the review and revision of the WOTUS rule a priority.
I am deeply concerned about threats to Jewish Community Centers across our country. Religious freedom is a core American principle.
Wishing a happy 76th birthday to @USCGReserve today
1/ I appreciate the interest in the VISA Act, legislation I introduced earlier today.
I stand with @IchooselifeFW & majrty of Americans calling 2 end Planned Parenthood's taxpayer funding. Abortion isn’t health care #ProtestPP
Congratulations to @RepTomPrice on becoming HHS Secretary. Dr. Price is the right leader to lead effort to repeal + replace Obamacare.
1/ @HASCRepublicans hearing today, the Vice Chiefs from each branch of military delivered some sobering statistics on our military readiness
Iran must face consequences for its continued aggressive behavior and destabilizing actions.
1/ The Obama administration assured the American people that the Iran Deal was a major step towards peace and nonproliferation
Judge Gorsuch will faithfully defend the Constitution and is a home run selection by @POTUS.
Glad to celebrate education freedom during #CatholicSchoolsWeek with @BishopDwengerHS, @BishopLuers and families across @diocesefwsb
My hope is that President Trump will follow past precedent and make certain DNI is in the room when national security decisions are made.
Our nation will be best served with @SenDanCoats by the President’s side as national security policies are developed and implemented.
I applaud actions taken today by @POTUS to enforce our immigration laws and ensure that securing our border is a national priority.
I commend Trump Administration's restoration of Mexico City Policy- will save lives & protect American taxpayers from paying for abortions.
President Obama's commutation of Manning's sentence sends terrible message that it's ok to leak classified info & endanger lives of troops.
Excited to report to my friend @JohnMcGauley that I have been named to the House Science, Space, and Technology Committee @HouseScience
Thanks @RepLukeMesser @SusanWBrooks @RepWalorski @ToddRokita @RepLarryBucshon @RepTrey for supporting my effort to join @HASCRepublicans

text: Wishing all the best to @GovHolcomb on his first day in office. That first gubernatorial @McDonalds meal looked like a good choice.
Prayers go out to families of four Israeli soldiers killed in suspected terrorist truck attack today in Jerusalem.
I am honored to have been named to the steering committee of the @RepublicanStudy Committee.
Today I supported #REINS Act → would require fed agencies to get approval from Congress and POTUS before implementing major rules.
Voted YES on H Res 11 to condemn action taken by U.N. Sec. Council last month on Israel - America must stand with #Israel. #IStandWithIsrael
Excited to have another #Hoosier close to the next POTUS. Congrats @SenDanCoats on Director of National Intelligence nomination!
Congrats to my friend @RepWalorski on being named to @WaysandMeansGOP . She will be a strong advocate for Indiana in this important role.
